        principle: "**Volumetric Centrifugal Fat Separation** — using acid hydrolysis + centrifugal force.\n\n**Detailed Chemical & Physical Process:**\n\n**Step 1: Acid Addition (Chemical Phase)**\n- Concentrated H₂SO₄ (density: **1.820–1.825 g/mL**, ≈**90–91% w/w**) add kiya jaata hai\n- H₂SO₄ do kaam karta hai:\n  (a) **Protein Digestion:**\n  $$\text{Casein (micellar)} + H_2SO_4 \rightarrow \text{Dissolved peptides} + \text{Heat released}$$\n  (b) **Fat Globule Liberation:** Fat globule membrane (MFGM — Milk Fat Globule Membrane, jo phospholipids + proteins se bana hota hai) ko dissolve karta hai → free fat globules release\n- Reaction **exothermic** hai — temperature **~70–80°C** tak pahunch jaati hai, jo fat ko pighla deti hai (liquid state mein laati hai)\n\n**Step 2: Amyl Alcohol Addition**\n- **n-Amyl alcohol** (1 mL) milaya jaata hai\n- Yeh fat-acid interface par surface tension ko kam karta hai\n- Fat ko stem mein **clean, sharp layer** mein collect hone mein madad karta hai\n- Charring (kala hona) rokta hai\n\n**Step 3: Centrifugation**\n- **Gerber Centrifuge:** 1100–1200 RPM par **5 minutes** (65°C par)\n- Generated **Relative Centrifugal Force (RCF):**\n$$RCF = \frac{r \cdot n^2}{895}$$\nWhere $r$ = radius (cm), $n$ = RPM\n- RCF ≈ **350–550 × g**\n- Fat (density: **~0.93 g/mL**) acid solution (density: **~1.43 g/mL**) se **alag ho jaata hai** — lighter fat upar aata hai\n\n**Step 4: Reading**\n- Butyrometer ko **65°C water bath** mein 3–5 min rakha jaata hai (fat ko liquid state mein rakhne ke liye)\n- Fat column ki height = **direct % fat reading**\n- Calibrated stem mein **0.1% divisions** — readable fat % directly\n\n**Error Sources:**\n- Wrong H₂SO₄ density (most critical)\n- Incorrect sample volume (10.75 mL ± 0.05 mL)\n- Incomplete mixing\n- Reading at wrong temperature",
