        principle: "**Centrifugal Sedimentation** — gravitational force ko magnify karna.\n\n**Fundamental Physics:**\n\n**Centrifugal Force:**\n$$F_c = m \cdot \omega^2 \cdot r$$\nWhere:\n- $m$ = mass of particle\n- $\omega$ = angular velocity (rad/s) = $\frac{2\pi \cdot RPM}{60}$\n- $r$ = radius of rotation (m)\n\n**Relative Centrifugal Force (RCF) or 'g-force':**\n$$RCF = \frac{\omega^2 \cdot r}{g} = \frac{(2\pi \cdot n)^2 \cdot r}{g \cdot 3600} = \frac{11.18 \cdot r \cdot n^2}{100^2}$$\nSimplified: $RCF = 1.118 \times 10^{-5} \times r(cm) \times RPM^2$\n\n**Example:** 3000 RPM, r = 15 cm:\n$$RCF = 1.118 \times 10^{-5} \times 15 \times (3000)^2 = 1510 \times g$$\n\n**Sedimentation Rate (Stokes' Law):**\n$$v_s = \frac{2r_p^2 (\rho_p - \rho_m) \cdot \omega^2 \cdot R}{9\eta}$$\nWhere:\n- $r_p$ = particle radius\n- $\rho_p$ = particle density\n- $\rho_m$ = medium density\n- $\eta$ = viscosity of medium\n- $\omega^2 R$ = centrifugal acceleration\n\n**Key Insight:** Larger particles aur denser particles **faster sediment** karte hain. Is liye high-fat milk mein fat globules (large, low density) jaldi separate ho jaate hain.\n\n**Rotor Types:**\n- **Fixed-angle rotor:** Tubes tilted at 25–45° — compact, high speed possible\n- **Swinging-bucket rotor:** Tubes swing horizontal during spin — better separation, lower max speed\n- **Continuous flow rotor:** Large volumes process karne ke liye\n\n**Safety Features:**\n- **Imbalance detection:** Automatic shutdown if samples not balanced (difference <0.1g)\n- **Lid interlock:** Cannot open during spinning\n- **Over-speed protection:** Electronic brake system",
