        purpose: "Microbial colony counting accuracy badhana aur human error kam karna:\n\n**Standard Tests Requiring Colony Counting:**\n- **Standard Plate Count (SPC) / Total Plate Count (TPC):** FSSAI method — Raw milk: ≤5×10⁵ CFU/mL acceptable\n- **Coliform Count:** <10 CFU/mL in pasteurized milk\n- **Yeast & Mold Count:** <50 CFU/g in cheese\n- **Somatic Cell Count (SCC):** >500,000 cells/mL = mastitis indicator\n\n**Countable Range:**\nStatistically valid results require **30–300 colonies per plate** (APHA standard)\n- <30 colonies = **TFTC** (Too Few To Count) — not statistically significant\n- >300 colonies = **TNTC** (Too Numerous To Count) — overlap errors",
        principle: "**Illuminated magnification + electronic counting system.**\n\n**Manual Colony Counter Components:**\n\n**1. Illumination System:**\n- **LED backlight base** (bottom illumination, 5000–6500K color temperature)\n- Creates **contrast** between transparent/translucent colonies and agar background\n- Roshni plate se neeche aati hai → bacteria ke opaque colonies dark background par clearly dikhte hain\n\n**2. Wolffhuegel Grid:**\n- Grid plate par printed — **20 equal segments** (each = 1/20 of standard plate)\n- Systematic counting karna aasaan hota hai — ek segment gino, phir ×20 karo\n- Helps avoid counting same colony twice\n\n**3. Magnification:**\n- Adjustable **1.5–2x magnifying glass** — small, pin-point colonies bhi visible\n\n**4. Electronic Counting Probe:**\n- Pressure-sensitive probe — touch se circuit complete → **digital counter increments by 1**\n- Audible beep = confirmation of count\n- Memory function — multiple plates ka data store\n\n**Advanced: Automatic Colony Counters (Image Analysis):**\n- **CCD/CMOS camera** plate ka high-resolution image leta hai\n- **Image analysis software** (using algorithms like Watershed Segmentation, Hough Circle Transform):\n  $$I_{threshold} \rightarrow \text{Binary image} \rightarrow \text{Colony identification} \rightarrow \text{Count}$$\n- Colony size, color, morphology bhi record kar sakta hai\n- Speed: **<5 seconds** per plate vs 5–15 minutes manual\n\n**Colony Count Calculation:**\n$$CFU/mL = \frac{\text{Average colonies counted}}{\text{Dilution factor} \times \text{Volume plated (mL)}}$$\n\nExample: 125 colonies on 10⁻⁴ dilution, 1 mL plated:\n$$CFU/mL = \frac{125}{10^{-4} \times 1} = 1.25 \times 10^6\ CFU/mL$$",
