        name: "Conductivity Meter",
        purpose: "Solution ki **electrical conductivity (EC)** maapna — ions ki presence ka direct indicator:\n\n**Dairy Lab Applications:**\n- **Mastitis Detection:** Mastitis-affected milk ki conductivity: **>6.0 mS/cm** (normal: 4.0–5.5 mS/cm) — inflammation se Na⁺, Cl⁻ ions milk mein badhte hain\n- **CIP Monitoring:** \n  - Alkaline detergent (NaOH): High conductivity (>10 mS/cm)\n  - Final rinse water (DM water): <20 µS/cm → clean rinse confirmed\n- **Water Quality:** RO/DI water conductivity: <1 µS/cm (USP Purified Water standard)\n- **Cheese Brine Concentration:** NaCl solution (18–20% = ~170 mS/cm)\n\n**Units:**\n- µS/cm (microSiemens/cm) — very pure water\n- mS/cm (milliSiemens/cm) — typical lab solutions\n- S/m (SI unit) — 1 S/m = 10 mS/cm",
        principle: "**Electrolytic Conductance Measurement** using AC impedance method.\n\n**Fundamental Concept:**\nElectrolyte solution mein ions vidyut ke carrier hote hain:\n$$G = \frac{1}{R} = \sigma \cdot \frac{A}{l}$$\nWhere:\n- $G$ = Conductance (Siemens, S)\n- $R$ = Resistance (Ohms, Ω)\n- $\sigma$ = Conductivity (S/m or S/cm)\n- $A$ = Electrode area (cm²)\n- $l$ = Distance between electrodes (cm)\n\n**Cell Constant (K):**\n$$K = \frac{l}{A} \quad (cm^{-1})$$\n$$\\sigma = G \times K$$\n\n**Why AC (Alternating Current)?**\n- DC current use karne se **electrolysis** ho jaayega (ions electrode par deposit/react ho jaayenge) → solution composition change → inaccurate reading\n- AC current (typically **1–10 kHz frequency**) ions ko ek direction mein nahi dhakelta → no electrolysis → accurate measurement\n\n**4-Electrode System (Advanced):**\n- 2 **outer electrodes** → current inject karte hain\n- 2 **inner electrodes** → voltage drop measure karte hain\n- Benefit: Electrode polarization effect eliminate hota hai → more accurate at high conductivity ranges\n\n**Temperature Compensation:**\nConductivity temperature ke saath significantly badlati hai:\n$$\\sigma_T = \\sigma_{25} \\times [1 + \\alpha(T - 25)]$$\nWhere $\\alpha$ ≈ **2% per °C** for most ionic solutions\nModern meters automatically 25°C par temperature-compensated reading display karte hain.\n\n**Ion Contribution to Conductivity (Equivalent Ionic Conductances at 25°C):**\n| Ion | λ (S·cm²/mol) |\n|---|---|\n| H⁺ | 349.8 (highest) |\n| OH⁻ | 198.3 |\n| Na⁺ | 50.1 |\n| Cl⁻ | 76.4 |\n| Ca²⁺ | 59.5 |",
        imageHint: "conductivity meter electrode four-cell probe",
