        name: "Desiccator",
        purpose: "Moisture-sensitive samples, chemicals, aur glassware ko **zero-humidity environment** mein store/cool karna:\n\n**Critical Use Cases:**\n- **Ash content analysis:** Crucible ko muffle furnace (550°C) se nikaalne ke baad, directly kamre ki hawa mein thanda nahi kar sakte — atmospheric moisture absorb ho jaayegi → weight gain → false high ash %\n- **Moisture analysis samples:** Aluminum pans ko moisture-free cool karna\n- **Hygroscopic chemicals:** Anhydrous CaCl₂, NaOH pellets, P₂O₅\n- **Reference weights:** Calibration weights ko dust aur moisture se protect karna\n\n**Types:**\n- **Standard glass desiccator:** Room temperature\n- **Vacuum desiccator:** With stopcock for evacuation\n- **Plastic desiccator:** Shatterproof, transparent\n- **Auto-desiccator:** Continuous humidity monitoring + display",
        principle: "**Adsorption/Absorption of Water Vapor by Desiccants** in a sealed environment.\n\n**Common Desiccants & Their Properties:**\n| Desiccant | Type | Capacity | Final RH | Color Change |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Silica Gel | Adsorption (physical) | 20–30% own weight | 10–20% | Blue→Pink (indicating type) |\n| Anhydrous CaCl₂ | Absorption (chemical) | 100% own weight | <5% | None |\n| P₂O₅ (Phosphorus pentoxide) | Chemical | Extremely high | <0.001% | None |\n| Drierite (CaSO₄) | Chemical | ~6% | ~0.005% | Blue→Pink |\n| Molecular Sieves (3Å, 4Å) | Adsorption | Moderate | <1% | None |\n\n**Silica Gel Mechanism (Most Common):**\n- Chemical formula: $SiO_2 \\cdot nH_2O$ — amorphous, porous structure\n- Surface area: **600–800 m²/g** — enormous for water vapor adsorption\n- Water molecules physically adsorb (van der Waals forces) onto silica surface:\n$$SiO_2\\text{-surface} + H_2O \\rightarrow $SiO_2\\text{-surface}\\cdots H_2O \\quad (\\text{physical adsorption})$$\n- **Indicating silica gel:** Cobalt chloride (CoCl₂) impregnated\n$$CoCl_2 \\cdot 6H_2O \\text{ (pink)} \\xrightarrow{heat/dry} CoCl_2 \\text{ (blue)}$$\n\n**Vacuum Desiccator:**\n$$P_{inside} \\downarrow \\Rightarrow \\text{Water's boiling point} \\downarrow \\Rightarrow \\text{Faster evaporation from sample}$$\nAt 0.1 atm → water boils at ~46°C → heat-sensitive samples bhi dry ho jaate hain\n\n**Equilibration Time:**\n- Hot crucible (550°C se) ko desiccator mein **minimum 30–45 minutes** cool karna chahiye before weighing\n- Cooling curve follows Newton's Law of Cooling:\n$$T(t) = T_{ambient} + (T_0 - T_{ambient})e^{-kt}$$",
