        id: "fume_hood",
        name: "Fume Hood",
        purpose: "**Chemical hazard protection** aur **contamination prevention:**\n\n**Hazardous Operations Requiring Fume Hood:**\n- **Kjeldahl Digestion:** H₂SO₄ fumes, SO₃ gas (TLV: 0.2 ppm)\n- **Gerber Method:** H₂SO₄ vapors, amyl alcohol fumes\n- **Soxhlet Extraction:** Petroleum ether, hexane (flammable, TLV: 500 ppm)\n- **COD Digestion:** Dichromate vapors (carcinogenic)\n- **Acid/Base preparation:** HCl, HNO₃, NaOH\n- **Standard solution preparation:** Mercury compounds (highly toxic)\n\n**Regulatory Standards:**\n- **OSHA 29 CFR 1910.1450** (Chemical Hygiene)\n- **ASHRAE 110:** Fume hood performance standard\n- **EN 14175:** European standard",
        principle: "**Negative Pressure Ventilation with Controlled Airflow** — containment through inward air velocity.\n\n**Key Performance Parameter — Face Velocity:**\n$$v_{face} = \\frac{Q_{exhaust}}{A_{sash\\ opening}}$$\n- **Minimum required:** 0.5 m/s (100 fpm) at sash opening\n- **Recommended:** 0.4–0.6 m/s (80–120 fpm)\n- **Too low (<0.4 m/s):** Containment failure — fumes escape to lab\n- **Too high (>0.6 m/s):** Turbulence inside hood → can pull fumes out; energy waste\n\n**Airflow Principle:**\n$$Q_{exhaust} > Q_{supply}$$\n$$\\Rightarrow P_{hood} < P_{lab} \\quad (\\text{Negative pressure inside hood})$$\n$$\\Rightarrow \\text{Air always flows INTO hood (inward flow)}$$\n\n**Hood Design Types:**\n1. **Constant Air Volume (CAV):** Fixed exhaust rate — simple but energy-inefficient\n2. **Variable Air Volume (VAV):** Sash position sensor → exhaust rate adjusts automatically → energy-efficient\n   - When sash down: Less opening → exhaust reduces → **energy saved** while maintaining face velocity\n\n**Exhaust Airflow Path:**\n$$\\text{Lab Air} \\xrightarrow{\\text{inward}} \\text{Hood Working Area} \\xrightarrow{\\text{baffle}} \\text{Exhaust plenum} \\xrightarrow{\\text{ductwork}} \\text{Roof fan} \\xrightarrow{\\text{scrubber/filter}} \\text{Atmosphere}$$\n\n**Alarm Systems:**\n- **Sash position alarm:** If sash too high → audible warning\n- **Low airflow alarm:** If face velocity drops below threshold\n- **Airflow monitor:** Magnehelic gauge or differential pressure sensor continuously monitors\n\n**HEPA-filtered Recirculating Fume Hood (Ductless):**\n- Exhaust ko bahar nahi jaane deta\n- Activated carbon + HEPA filter se chemicals remove karke air wapas lab mein release karta hai\n- For non-acid, non-perchloric acid work only",
