            description: '**Construction:** Long, narrow graduated tube (usually 50 mL) with a PTFE stopcock at the bottom.\n**Accuracy (Class A):** ±0.05 mL (50 mL burette).\n**Least Count:** 0.1 mL graduation; readable to 0.02 mL by interpolation.\n**Use:** Titration — dispensing titrant in controlled, measured drops.\n**Reading:** Read the bottom of the meniscus; zero is at the top.\n**Error:** Air bubbles in the tip cause false volume readings; always check before titration.'
